---
// QiskitCircuit.astro — First Qiskit quantum circuit example
---

<div class="qsk-wrap">
  <h3 class="qsk-title">Your First Quantum Circuit in Qiskit</h3>
  <p class="qsk-sub">Four lines of Python. One Bell state. Welcome to quantum programming.</p>

  <div class="qsk-steps">
    <div class="qsk-step" style="--i:0">
      <div class="qsk-num">1</div>
      <div class="qsk-content">
        <div class="qsk-what">Install Qiskit</div>
        <pre class="qsk-code"><code>pip install qiskit qiskit-aer</code></pre>
        <div class="qsk-why">Qiskit is IBM's open-source quantum SDK. Aer is the simulator.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="qsk-step" style="--i:1">
      <div class="qsk-num">2</div>
      <div class="qsk-content">
        <div class="qsk-what">Create a circuit</div>
        <pre class="qsk-code"><code>from qiskit import QuantumCircuit

qc = QuantumCircuit(2, 2)  # 2 qubits, 2 classical bits
qc.h(0)                     # Hadamard on qubit 0
qc.cx(0, 1)                 # CNOT: control=0, target=1
qc.measure([0, 1], [0, 1])  # Measure both qubits</code></pre>
        <div class="qsk-why">H gate creates superposition. CNOT entangles the qubits. Measure reads the result.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
    <div class="qsk-step" style="--i:2">
      <div class="qsk-num">3</div>
      <div class="qsk-content">
        <div class="qsk-what">Run on simulator</div>
        <pre class="qsk-code"><code>from qiskit_aer import AerSimulator

sim = AerSimulator()
result = sim.run(qc, shots=1000).result()
print(result.get_counts())
# &#123;'00': 498, '11': 502&#125;</code></pre>
        <div class="qsk-why">~50% chance of 00, ~50% chance of 11. Never 01 or 10. That's entanglement.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<style>
  .qsk-wrap{background:linear-gradient(135deg,#0f172a,#1e293b);border-radius:16px;padding:2rem;margin:2rem 0;border:1px solid #334155}
  .qsk-title{color:#f1f5f9;font-size:1.15rem;font-weight:700;margin:0 0 .25rem}
  .qsk-sub{color:#64748b;font-size:.78rem;margin:0 0 1.5rem;font-family:monospace}
  .qsk-steps{display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:12px}
  .qsk-step{display:flex;gap:12px;align-items:flex-start;opacity:0;animation:qskIn .4s ease forwards;animation-delay:calc(var(--i)*.15s)}
  .qsk-num{width:24px;height:24px;border-radius:50%;background:rgba(6,182,212,.12);color:#06b6d4;font-size:.65rem;font-weight:700;display:flex;align-items:center;justify-content:center;flex-shrink:0;margin-top:4px;font-family:monospace}
  .qsk-content{flex:1}
  .qsk-what{color:#f1f5f9;font-size:.78rem;font-weight:600;margin-bottom:.5rem}
  .qsk-code{background:rgba(0,0,0,.3);border:1px solid #334155;border-radius:8px;padding:10px 14px;margin:0 0 .5rem;overflow-x:auto}
  .qsk-code code{color:#4ade80;font-size:.68rem;font-family:monospace;line-height:1.6;white-space:pre}
  .qsk-why{color:#94a3b8;font-size:.68rem;line-height:1.5}
  @keyframes qskIn{from{opacity:0;transform:translateX(-10px)}to{opacity:1;transform:translateX(0)}}
</style>
